238
00:12:36,321 --> 00:12:39,597
- Sharing with who?
- I don't know.

239
00:12:39,681 --> 00:12:41,797
Get some nice young couple.

240
00:12:41,881 --> 00:12:44,349
- Took me a while to get used to you.
- Oh, thank you(!)

241
00:12:44,481 --> 00:12:48,030
(Man) There's 200,000 more families
in London than homes to put them.

242
00:12:48,121 --> 00:12:53,115
And there's 60,000 single persons
living without sinks or stoves.

243
00:12:53,201 --> 00:12:56,034
In seven central London boroughs,

244
00:12:56,121 --> 00:12:58,077
one in ten of all households
is overcrowded,

245
00:12:58,161 --> 00:13:01,358
with more than 1.5 people per room.

246
00:13:01,441 --> 00:13:03,796
Oh, hello, is your room
still to let?

247
00:13:03,881 --> 00:13:06,236
No, is it still in that place?

248
00:13:06,321 --> 00:13:07,310
Yes, it is.

249
00:13:07,401 --> 00:13:12,395
Well, it'll be a week tomorrow
since I told them to take it out.

250
00:13:12,481 --> 00:13:14,995
- Pardon?
- It'll be a week...

251
00:13:15,081 --> 00:13:19,677
On Thursday, I asked them to take
