252
00:13:19,761 --> 00:13:22,036
A few years back,
figures released by the LCC

253
00:13:22,121 --> 00:13:24,271
revealed that families
of certain sizes

254
00:13:24,361 --> 00:13:29,594
would be 350 years on the housing
list before being offered a house.

255
00:13:29,681 --> 00:13:31,672
Oh, it's a scourge here.

256
00:13:31,761 --> 00:13:35,310
The present target of 500,000 set
by government is not high enough.

257
00:13:35,401 --> 00:13:38,791
Even if it is reached, there's still
people living in slums in ten years.

258
00:13:38,881 --> 00:13:43,909
The government must realise this is
a crisis and treat it as such.

259
00:13:44,001 --> 00:13:48,472
We can't stay at Mum's.
The council said it was overcrowded.

260
00:13:48,561 --> 00:13:52,998
They needn't find out, need they?
Oh, Mum'll fix it, don't worry.

261
00:13:53,081 --> 00:13:56,073
You're gonna have better eyes
than your dad, aren't you? Eh?

262
00:13:56,161 --> 00:13:58,436
Yeah, he's squinting a bit, though.

263
00:13:59,481 --> 00:14:01,437
- They all squint.
- Oh.

264
00:14:01,521 --> 00:14:04,718
(Cathy) Funny how a baby
makes a place quite different.

265
00:14:04,801 --> 00:14:06,757
And Reggie said so, too.

266
00:14:06,841 --> 00:14:08,957
Well, goodbye to freedom.

267
00:14:09,041 --> 00:14:10,997
I didn't mind, though.

268
00:14:13,441 --> 00:14:15,159
(Women chatter)

269
00:14:15,921 --> 00:14:19,231
(Man) This is what you call
the island of paradise.

270
00:14:19,321 --> 00:14:23,758
Kiddies here have seen rats running
around the place as big as cats.

271
00:14:29,001 --> 00:14:31,037
(Dog barks)

272
00:14:32,921 --> 00:14:35,993
(Woman) Any time the children
have accidents,

273
00:14:36,081 --> 00:14:40,757
most times all the mothers come
down to see if they can help.

274
00:14:40,841 --> 00:14:44,834
(Old woman) The damned places
are so old, they want pulling down!

275
00:14:45,121 --> 00:14:47,191
(Woman) We've got plenty of company.

276
00:14:47,281 --> 00:14:50,956
I think we're reasonable people,
that we all get on together.

277
00:14:51,041 --> 00:14:54,113
We have our ups and downs,
you can fight over the kids,

278
00:14:54,201 --> 00:14:58,035
but apart from that, we're lucky,
I suppose, better off than some.

279
00:14:58,121 --> 00:15:01,272
(Old woman) I don't like
half of the people in it,

280
00:15:01,361 --> 00:15:04,671
and what is more there's
none of 'em neighbourly.

281
00:15:04,761 --> 00:15:09,039
They've always got something to say
about you behind your back.

282
00:15:09,121 --> 00:15:11,954
(Woman) I had a friend
lived next door to me,

283
00:15:12,041 --> 00:15:15,556
she really would have give?1,000
